<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Recorded in Bering Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measured
7.6 magnitude struck the Bering Sea this morning, prompting
officials to warn of a possible tidal wave off Alaska.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which struck at about 2:27 a.m. local time (1127
GMT), was centered 130 kilometers off the coast of the Kamchatka
Peninsula in eastern Russia, an Associated Press report said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damage. 
</P>
