<HEADLINE> 70 Minute Blackout in Many Parts of Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Electricity in many parts of
Sri Lanka had been shut down for 70 minutes tonight due to unknown
reasons.
</P>
<P>
The blackout hit Colombo this evening at around 8 o'clock local
time.
</P>
<P>
Electricity supply was restored 70 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Bandalawela city in the central part of Sri Lanka
was also affected by the blackout.
</P>
<P>
Well-informed sources here said power supply to many other
parts of the country was also cut off.
</P>
<P>
Other sources said the blackout was due to technical reasons.
But the Ceylon Electricity Board, which is in charge of the
electricity supply throughout the country, was not immediately
available for comment.
</P>
<P>
At the time of the incident, a slight thunder storm was taking
place in the area.
</P>
<P>
There were high speculations among the citizens in Colombo that
there might be an LTTE background behind the incident.  
</P>
</TEXT>
