<HEADLINE> NDF Gives 6.5-Million Loan to Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican government and
the Nordic Development Fund (NDF) today signed an agreement,
under which the NDF will provide a loan of 6.5 million U.S.
Dollars to Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
The loan is aimed at funding the National Project of Water
Development which started in Mozambique in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The project, at a cost of 57 million U.S. Dollars in total,
includes organizational development of the water sector,
sustainable management of water resources and sustainable supply
of water in the rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican Planning and Finance Minister Tomaz Salomao and NDF
President Jens Lund-Sorense inked the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Salomao said after his signature that the loan will help the
Mozambican government implement and develop its national water
policy.
</P>
<P>
This will be the fourth NDF loan to Mozambique. The NDF has
loaned 22 million U.S. Dollars to Mozambique so far. 
</P>
