<HEADLINE> One Ukrainian Burned to Death at Somali Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A Ukrainian national was
killed and an Indian was wounded when fire caught their
commercial vessel at the port town of Merca of Somalia on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports available today, a man identified
as Mr Ruslan only who was an engineer had died for his wounds as
a result of a cooking gas explosion in the kitchen of the vessel.
</P>
<P>
Doctors in Merca general hospital, 100 km south of the capital
Mogadishu, said the deceased had received major flame wounds in
the stomach and the chest.
</P>
<P>
"He was given the necessary treatment, but unfortunately we
could not save his life since the fire went deep into his heart,"
said one of the doctors.
</P>
<P>
Another engineer, Gurprees Bhinder Puran, an Indian national,
was also wounded by the fire as he tried to help his burning
colleague, late Ruslan.
</P>
<P>
Puran is now receiving treatment in the hospital of Merca run
by the Italian aid agency, Commitato Servicio Voluntare(COSV).
</P>
<P>
The crew of the ship have managed to extinguish the fire which
endangered the commodities on board and the vessel itself. The
local businessmen who chartered the vessel, MV-Flash, yesterday
started off-loading the sugar they bought from Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, at least five people were killed and 22 others were
wounded after two vehicles collided at km-13 resort restaurant of
southwestern Mogadishu today.
</P>
<P>
The vehicles, a civilian bus and a big trailer from Afgoe town
road crushed leading to the death on the spot of five passengers,
all men, on the bus.
</P>
<P>
All the wounded, heavy and slight, were transported to
Mogadishu where they are being treated in hospitals.
</P>
<P>
This is one of the most serious road accidents in the war
ravaged country of Somalia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
