<DOCNO> XIE19971206.0033 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WTO Group of Developing Countries Fully Supports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The informal group of developing
countries in the World Trade Organization (WTO) today expressed
their wish that China should join the WTO at an early date.
</P>
<P>
Following is the full text of the group's statement made here
today after consultations among the developing country members who
account for a majority of the current 132 WTO members:
</P>
<P>
The accession of the People's Republic of China to the WTO is
important both for the multilateral trading system and for the
developing countries.
</P>
<P>
The group of developing countries in the WTO, therefore, fully
supports the expeditious completion of the process for China's
accession to the WTO, and hopes to see China as a full member of
the organization at the earliest possible date. 
</P>
</TEXT>
