<HEADLINE> Kamchatka Hit by Strong Earthquake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 5 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake with tremors
measuring 8-9 on the Richter scale rocked the Kamchatka Bay basin
at 14:26 Moscow time (1126 GMT) today, according to the Itar-Tass
news agency.
</P>
<P>
The quake's coordinates were 55.8 northern latitude, 162.1
eastern longitude, the press service of the Russian Ministry for
Emergency Situations was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Tremors measured 5 in the city of Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky and
4 in Severo-Kurilsk, Russia's Far East, the report said.
</P>
<P>
There were also continuous tremors between 14:48 and 15:10
Moscow time (1148 and 1210 GMT) scoring 5 to 7 on the Richter
scale.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the epicenter of the earthquake was 10
kilometers deep and located in an area 300 kilometers from
Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky.
</P>
<P>
A regional emergency service duty officer was cited as
reporting that there were no victims or destruction in
Petropavlovsk and Ust-Kamchatsk, a settlement located closer to
the epicenter, at a 170 kilometer distance. 
</P>
