<HEADLINE> France Calls for Unity of Group of Contact for Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 5 (Xinhua) -- France today called for the
maintenance of unity among the five member countries of the Group
of Contact for Bosnia: the United States, France, Britain, Russia
and Germany.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said
that the unity of the Contact Group is essential for an efficient
international action to respond to a crisis in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
"France has as an objective to constantly see to the
maintenance of the unity of the Group of Contact," said the
spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
She said that a number of decisions on the application of the
Dayton peace agreement have not been implemented and remain on the
table, such as the laws on citizenship and passports, the
functioning of the council of ministers, the common currency and
car registration plates.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the five countries will meet next week
in Bonn, which was described as "an essential step" by German
Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel and his French counterpart, Hubert
Vedrine, during their visit to Bosnia Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel and Vedrine have called on the three members of the
Bosnian presidency to implement a series of issues in the civil
part of the Dayton peace agreement, which always remains suspended
after the signing of the agreement at the end of 1995.
</P>
<P>
France and Germany said that there is no alternative to the
Dayton agreement for solving the Bosnia problem. 
</P>
