<HEADLINE> UK New Car Sales Hit Record in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 5 (Xinhua) -- New Car sales in Britain hit a
new record last month to stand at 153,323, up from 135,342 a year
ago and a 12.5 percent year-on-year rise, according to figures
released by the Society of Motor Manufacturers and Traders (SMMT)
today.
</P>
<P>
The SMMT said that new car sales for the first 11 months of
this year have reached 2,086,091, a 7.1 percent rise on the same
period of last year and also above the previous third-highest
year, 1987.
</P>
<P>
However, the SMMT said that although there is still one month
left this year, it is not possible for this year's market to reach
the 2.2 million units of 1988.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that there were no other special factors for
last month's sale surge except for the stiff competition between
more than 50 companies.
</P>
<P>
Figures also showed that the market share of imports was also
one of the highest recorded, accounting for 65 percent of the
total number in November and 66 percent for the year. 
</P>
