<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, London Ends at 6-Week High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe
ended mixed Friday, with London surging to a six-week closing high
while Paris finishing slightly weaker.
</P>
<P>
British shares in London closed comfortably above the
5,100-point level on the back of gains in New York, with the FTSE
100 index 60.0 points higher at 5,142.9, a rise of 311.1 points
from last week.
</P>
<P>
Wall Street managed to shrug off a huge leap in US non-farm
payrolls despite its likely impact on U.S. interest rates, which
helped the London market to recover from its early afternoon dip.
</P>
<P>
The London market has seen a volatile day, with the FTSE 100
index see-sawing between a 34-point fall and 96-point advance.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that increased liquidity helped stoke the
traditional year-end rally.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, French shares closed the session firmer, but off
the day's highs, in quiet trade ahead of key U.S. jobs data, with
the DAX-30 index up 30.28 points at 4,170.08, 220.94 points higher
on last Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, the CAC-40 index in Paris ended 4.36 points lower at
2,910.09, but still a rise of 50.90 from a week ago. Dealers said
that robust U.S. unemployment data unsettled French stocks
although the firm dollar provided some support. 
