<HEADLINE> Cyprus Calls for More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot President Glafcos
Clerides today called for more foreign investment in the island,
which he described as an international business center.
</P>
<P>
During the last two decades, Cyprus has developed into an
international center of transit trade, tourism, offshore and
maritime activities, banking and business services, Clerides told
a seminar held in London on "Cyprus: an international business
center," the Cypriot News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, organized by the Cyprus Chamber of Commerce and
Industry, the Central Bank of Cyprus and the Confederation of
British Industries, was attended by more than 200 businessmen,
according to the agency.
</P>
<P>
Clerides cited as the advantages of Cyprus its macroeconomic
and social stability and cohesion, high educational level of the
manpower, modern facilities of transport and telecommunications,
and strong political, cultural and economic ties with Europe.
</P>
<P>
The president said Cyprus ranks the third in the Mediterranean
region in terms of per capita income, noting that it also enjoys
full employment and a balance of payments.
</P>
<P>
He said new opportunities are emerging for Cyprus to upgrade
and enhance its role as a base for foreign enterprises wishing to
enter the rapidly expanding markets in Middle East. 
</P>
