<HEADLINE> Chinese Lan Breaks Men's 54-kg World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, THAILAND, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese strongman
Lan Shizhang broke the world record by jerking 160.5 kilograms in
the men's 54-kg category at the 68th Men's World Weightlifting
Championships here late Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Lan bettered the previous world mark of 160 kgs set by Halil
Mutlu of Turkey in November, 1994.
</P>
<P>
Lan's mark will stand as the permanent record as the World
Weightlifting Federation is to reduce men's current 10 categories
to eight from 1998. 
