<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Plane Crashes into Residential Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 6 (Xinhua) -- A Russian military cargo plane
crashed today shortly after take-off from Irkutsk's airport,
killing all 46 people aboard and an estimated 150 on the ground.
</P>
<P>
The plane destroyed a four-story residential building that
contained 64 apartments in a satellite town in the city of Irkutsk
some 5,000 kilometers east of Moscow, when it hit the ground
around 09:40 Moscow time (06:40 GMT), reported the Itar-Tass news
agency.
</P>
<P>
The municipal housing department said about 200 people might
have been staying in the building when it was hit.
</P>
<P>
It also caused damage to another 100-apartment building,
several 16-apartment buildings, an orphanage and a school.
</P>
<P>
The 46 people killed in the plane were military personnel; 16
were crew members.
</P>
<P>
The Antonov An-124, named Ruslan, is reputed to be the world's
largest transport aircraft, which can carry 120 tons.
</P>
<P>
The plane was transporting two Sukhoi jet fighters to Vietnam
via Russia's Far Eastern port of Vladivostok.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin said he was shocked by news of
the crash and extended his condolences to the failies of the
victims.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin has dispatched Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin to
the scene of the accident and instructed him to conduct a probe
into the accident.
</P>
<P>
The crash may have been caused by the failure of the two left
engines of the cargo plane. The accident occurred at an altitude
of 70-meters, said sources close to the governmental probe
commission.
</P>
<P>
Rescue personnel and firefighters rushed to the site
immediately after the disaster took place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
