<DOCNO> XIE19971206.0063 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-06 13:55 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OIC Foreign Ministerial Meeting Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The foreign ministerial
meeting of the Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) opened
here this afternoon to prepare agenda and documents for the
eighth OIC summit to be opened Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the inaugural session, Iranian Foreign Minister
Kamal Kharrazi said that the Islamic World must pave the way and
prepare the necessary grounds for it "to play a historical role
in founding the future international order and participate in
its management within the framework and on the basis of
democratic cooperation."
</P>
<P>
The eighth OIC summit is to be held at a critical and
sensitive historical and international juncture at the threshold
of the third millennium, he said, tumultuous developments are
unfolding in the world and the Islamic world is also undergoing
fundamental transformations.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi noted that today's world depends on the peaceful
coexistence, cooperation and collective participation of all
pluralities and varieties in an institutionalized manner.
</P>
<P>
"Endowed with rich culture, tremendous manpower, enormous
resources and reserves and strategic position," he said, the
Islamic world "is poised to assume a paramount historical role
in shaping the new world order."
</P>
<P>
However, Kharrazi said, the degree of the Islamic World's
success in playing an active, creative, constructive and
participatory role in the management of the pluralistic world is
"directly and palpably related to the pace of its own growth and
development."
</P>
<P>
He underlined the need to elevate the general level of
knowledge, learning, education and awareness, to institutionalize
the process of confidence-building, to consolidate Islamic
solidarity, to expand bilateral, multinational and regional
relations and to attain comprehensive and balanced sustainable
development in the broad sense through collective participation.
</P>
<P>
"It is of crucial and urgent importance for the Organization
of Islamic Conference to address and deal with the wide range of
issues and problems in front of us in a practical and
action-and-result-oriented manner," Kharrazi said.
</P>
<P>
He named the issues of Palestine, Jerusalem, Afghanistan,
Bosnia-herzegovina as most serious problems in the Islamic
world, adding that it is also facing the challenge of promoting
political, economic, social and cultural cooperation among
Islamic countries.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi called for collective efforts by the Islamic
countries during the OIC summit to solve the problems of the
Islamic World.
</P>
<P>
He also assured the participants in the meeting that Iran, as
the OIC chairman, would work "with all its disposal in the
course of the current session as well as through the next three
years" to realize the ideals and objectives of the OIC
organization and the eighth summit.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the inaugural ceremony, the foreign ministerial
meeting entered its closed session to discuss more than 140
resolutions concluded by the OIC experts meeting which ended
Friday.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the issues of relations between Islamic
countries and Israel would be the top topic for debates in the
coming two days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
