<HEADLINE> Russian Plane Crash Leaves More Than 100 Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 6 (Xinhua) -- A Russian military cargo plane
crashed today eight minutes after take-off from Irkutsk's airport
in Siberia. At least 46 people on board the aircraft were killed
and an estimated 150 died at the crash site on the ground.
</P>
<P>
Among the 46 people on board, 16 were crew members; the rest
were passengers, reported the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which crashed at 09:44 Moscow time (06:44 GMT),
ploughed into a four-story residential building in a satellite
town of the city of Irkutsk some 5,000 kilometers east of Moscow,
said the news agency.
</P>
<P>
The An-124 Ruslan plane, which can carry 120 tons of cargo, was
transporting two Sukhoi-27 fighter jets to Vietnam via Russia's
Far Eastern port of Vladivostok. 
</P>
