<HEADLINE> Hainan Province Holding Foreign Trade Talks Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 6 (Xinhua) -- China's island province of
Hainan is expected to hold a grand foreign trade and economic
talks in April 1998 as part of its 10th anniversary activities.
</P>
<P>
Hainan, which was officially designated as a province in April
of 1988, plans to provide opportunities in 100 major industrial
projects in iron and steel, tires, and upgrading the network of
urban electric power supplies in Haikou, the provincial capital,
and a garbage disposal project in the city of Sanya at the
southern tip of the island.
</P>
<P>
Since 1988, Hainan has gotten approximately seven billion US
dollars worth of investment from overseas and more than 30 billion
yuan (3.6 billion US dollars) from other parts of the country. The
total foreign trade volume has surpassed 15 billion US dollars.
</P>
