<HEADLINE> New Snowfall Gives Fresh Look To Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- A moderate snowfall last
night helped clean the air of Beijing without seriously disrupting
transportation.
</P>
<P>
The snow caused temporary traffic snarls when it started at 5
p.m. Friday, but didn't affect aircraft at Capital Airport, thanks
to over 300 workers and armed policemen who worked for 15 hours to
clean the two runways and 16 taxiways, with the help of
snow-movers and melting agents.
</P>
<P>
The snowfall turned to sleet in the early morning hours today,
and had melted in many parts of the city by this evening, and
municipal sanitation department sent several trucks out to spray
1,000 tons of saltwater on the streets to help melt the snow.
</P>
<P>
Temperatures in the Beijing area are down to nine or ten
degrees centigrade below zero.
</P>
<P>
Many people in Beijing didn't even get a chance to see the
snowy landscape because it melted so fast. One city bus employee
said that the number of passenger was not down noticeably from
ordinary weekends. 
</P>
</TEXT>
