<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Calls on Workers to Contribute to Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a ranking Communist
Party of China (CPC) official today urged trade union leaders to
arouse workers' enthusiasm about reforms in state-run enterprises,
especially about turning losses into profits and to complete the
tasks set forth during the recent 15th Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
In his address to the Fifth Session of the 12th Executive
Committee of the All-China Federation of Trade Unions (ACFTU),
which opened here Friday, Hu, a member of the Standing Committee
of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, said trade
unions should encourage workers to contribute to the development
of new products and technological improvements.
</P>
<P>
Finding jobs for laid-off workers is vital to the success of
state-run enterprise reforms, he noted, and trade unions should
provide more job opportunities and professional training for
laid-off workers, and encourage them to change their old ideas and
find new jobs themselves.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Hu asked trade unions to give priority to the
protection of the workers' rights and interests, and to keep in
mind the concrete interests of workers as a whole.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that trade union officials teach workers to
safeguard their own rights by using the law, and the democratic
appraisal of enterprise officials should be part of the overall
appraisal of State-run enterprise officials.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, also a member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and chairman of the
ACFTU, presided over the session, which was attended by more than
200 members of the ACFTU Executive Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
