<HEADLINE> New Photo Album About Life Of Peking Opera Master </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- A new photo album about the
life of the greatest master of Peking Opera, Mei Lanfang, has just
been published by Beijing Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
Mei, who was born in 1894 and died in 1961, greatly developed
the style of Peking Opera by founding the Mei school, and became
famous for playing female roles on.
</P>
<P>
The new book has 1,000 photos recording the life of this
legendary master, and his style of work. Senior officials, Mei's
relatives, students and friends attended a release ceremony today.
</P>
<P>
The 200-year-old Peking Opera, known as a national treasure,
has been declining in popularity since the 1980s as a result of
competition from newer forms of entertainment, and the Chinese
government has been trying to revive it. 
</P>
