<HEADLINE> Dar es Salaam: Most Expensive African City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian capital of Dar
es Salaam has been listed as the most expensive African city, in
which prices may even higher than those of Paris, "Business
Times" said today.
</P>
<P>
According to the new world classification of the cost of
living published by the Swiss firm Corporate Resources recently,
Dar es Salaam is the most expensive city in Africa, with an index
of 106.78 percent.
</P>
<P>
Dar es Salaam is the 19th most expensive city in the world.
This places it above such cities like Paris (104), Zurich (104),
Rio de Janeiro (103), "Business Times" quoted the firm's report
as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey conducted in 100 cities earlier this
year, the most expensive city in the world is Tokyo with an index
close to 170 points. The least expensive is the Indian city of
Madras with an index of 60.
</P>
<P>
The city of New York is calculated with an index of 100. This
means that an American visitor finds Dar es Salaam nearly seven
percent more expensive than New York.
</P>
<P>
After Tokyo the most expensive cities are Hong Kong (153.20),
Moscow (1513.03), Osaka (147.86) and Beijing (140.92).
</P>
<P>
The survey "housewife's basket," conducted by the Swiss
company, includes 200 items like food drinks, clothes, equipment,
accommodation, health, transportation and entertainment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
