<HEADLINE> China Establishes Harbor Engineering Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony in Beijing's Great
Hall of the People today marked the establishment of the China
Harbor Engineering Group.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Communications Huang Zhendong addressed the
ceremony, which was also attended by Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua,
saying that the ministry has made some progress in enterprise
reforms by turning transport and construction companies into six
large groups that can make these state-owned enterprises more
competitive, both domestically and internationally.
</P>
<P>
China Harbor Engineering Group is composed of the China Harbor
Engineering (Group) Company and ten subsidiary companies, with
assets of 17.2 billion yuan and at least 800,000 employees,
according to the company's president, Ye Huiran.
</P>
<P>
He said that all major coastal and river ports in China were
built by the company's subsidiaries and that they have been doing
business internationally since the '80s.
</P>
<P>
Their participation in the Macao International Airport Project,
as one of the major contractors, has made profits and earned an
international reputation.
</P>
<P>
The group works mainly in hydraulic engineering, dredging, and
manufacturing of port machinery, he said, but that it has become
more active in foreign trade, ship-building, transport, real
estate, financing, and investment.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, Ye said, the engineering company has been on the
list of Top 225 International Contractors of the US's "Engineering
News Record" magazine, and it is one of the top 500 service
companies in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
