<HEADLINE> Assets Management System Being Established In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 6 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
has basically set up a state assets management and supervisory
system designed to meet the needs of the market economy, according
to Chen Guixiang, director of the provincial State Assets
Administration.
</P>
<P>
The system covers statistics, property rights, evaluation, and
increasing the value of state assets, Chen said. The province had
120 assets evaluation agencies and more than 2,000 asset valuers
by the end of last year, who have appraised assets valued at more
than 180 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang had more than 170 billion yuan in state assets at the
end of last year, some 90 billion yuan of which were in
production. In the last five years the value of state assets in
enterprises grew 21.6 percent. To properly maintain state assets,
the province has formed nine enterprise groups.  
</P>
</TEXT>
