<HEADLINE> Chinese Dominate Second Day Speed Skating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese skaters showed their
undisputable domination in the 500-meter races of both men's and
women's sessions in the Japan Challenge Cup short track speed
skating competition on Saturday in Nobeyama, Japan.
</P>
<P>
Wang Chunlu from Jilin porvince won the all-Chinese women's
finals in 46.826 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Sun Dandan finished second with 0.096 seconds behind, followed
by two Yang Yangs, with the Yang of Heilongjiang province third
and the other of Jilin province fourth.
</P>
<P>
Chun Lee-Kyung of South Korea, who shared the world champion
with Yang of Heilongjiang in March, was eliminated in semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
In the men's final, An Yulong timed in 43.724, beating
compatriot Li Jiajun and three Japanese finalists.
</P>
<P>
Li finished runner-up in both the 1,500-meter and 500-meter
races to top the men's overall standigns with six points, followed
by An and Lee Jun-Hwan of South Korea who ranked second with five
points each.
</P>
<P>
Wang shared the women's top place with 1,500-meter winner Won
Hae-Kyung of South Korea with five points respectively, leading
world champion Yang in third by one point.
</P>
<P>
The three-day competition, which is the fifth and last leg of
ranking series counting towards the world championships in
February, will see its end on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The fourth leg in Seoul in November was cancelled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
