<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwestern China Region Becoming Leading Petrochemical Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, December 6 (Xinhua) -- China will spend 100 billion
yuan (12 billion US dollars) on exploration and development of oil
and gas resources in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region over the
next three years.
</P>
<P>
More than two million yuan (241,000 US dollars) will be used
for seven petrochemical bases producing chemical fiber, rubber,
plastics, nitrogenous fertilizer and methanol in Urumqi, Karamay,
Korla, Hami and other places.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang has a third of China's oil and gas reserves, with 45
oil and gasfields having a combined proven reserve of 2.1 billion
tons of oil and 360 billion cu.m. of gas.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 oil and gasfields are now in operation, with a
combined annual production capacity of 17 million tons of oil.
</P>
<P>
The autonomous region will raise its annual oil output to 23
million tons and gas output to three billion cu.m. by the end of
the century, at which time the region's oil and gas will be 16
percent of the national output.
</P>
<P>
Its annual output of synthetic fiber and synthetic resin will
increase from last year's 500,000 tons to 1.47 million tons,
nitrogenous fertilizer, to 3.16 million tons, and tires, to 1.2
million sets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
