<DOCNO> XIE19971206.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African Estate Industry Emphasizes Agents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 6 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's Estate
Agents Board (EAB) is considering re-introducing compulsory
examination for estate agents to improve its service, local daily
Saturday Star reported today
</P>
<P>
The EAB has proposed that the present system in which
candidate agents automatically obtain full status after a year
should also be abolished.
</P>
<P>
This follows a comprehensive review by the EAB of the current
education system for estate agents and its effectiveness in terms
of consumer protection.
</P>
<P>
EAB manager Andrew Harrison was quoted as saying that the
board did not want an exam system that is perceived as mere
compliance with a licensing requirement but one that is
recognized as a pro-active endeavor to provide meaningful
education to estate agents.
</P>
<P>
"We know that the proper education of estate agents is one of
the most important measures we have at our disposal in the
protection of consumers.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that education can only be meaningful if the
assimilation of knowledge and understanding is properly
examined," Harrison said.
</P>
<P>
Nationlink SA, the newest member of South African real estate
"big league" has wasted no time in establishing a heavy weight
training program.
</P>
<P>
In-house training is compulsory for, and free to, all
Nationlink agents, and the program is recognized as one of the
best and most consistent in the real estate industry, the company
said.
</P>
<P>
The program is intented to accommodate everyone from beginners
to highly experienced agents and starts with a three-day basic
course.
</P>
<P>
"After that, there are several modules to be completed,
including dealing with buyers, dealing with sellers, time
management and sole mandate. Next year we will be adding courses
on negotiation, marketing skills and, for agency principals,
management," training manager Hugo Steyn said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
