<HEADLINE> 9 Killed in 3 Train Explosions in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 6 (Xinhua) -- At least nine people were
killed and 69 others injured in three powerful bomb explosions
that ripped through the compartments of three trains in India's
Tamil Nadu and Kerala states today, Press Trust of India (PTI)
reported.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that three or five people were killed in
two blast incidents.
</P>
<P>
Police said that they suspected the hand of a religious
fundamentalist organization in the act.
</P>
<P>
Today is the fifth anniversary of the demolition of the
disputed mosque in Ayodhya of Uttar Pradesh in northern India by
the Hindu people. More than 1,000 people were killed in the
nation-wide violence following the demolition act five years ago.
</P>
<P>
Over 5,000 people were taken into preventive custody from
various parts of Tamil Nadu Friday as a precautionary measure to
ward off the trouble on the fifth anniversary of the Ayodhya
incident.
</P>
<P>
Muslim leaders in the state had made an appeal on the same day
to observe peace during the anniversary.  
</P>
</TEXT>
