<DOCNO> XIE19971206.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea's 12th Largest Conglomerate Goes Bankrupt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 6 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's 12th largest
conglomerate, Halla Group, was declared bankrupt Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Halla, with a gross asset of 326.2 billion won (about 282
million U.S. dollars), has piled up a debt totaling 6,476.4
billion won (5.6 billion U.S. dollars) borrowed from banks,
merchant banks, insurance companies and lease companies.
</P>
<P>
Halla's chief creditor Korea Exchange Bank (KEB) today
announced its decision to let the group go under, contributing its
failure to excessive investments in the newly-expanded
shipbuilding area.
</P>
<P>
The 16-affiliate Halla managed businesses in many fields
include chemicals, machinery, shipbuilding and construction.
</P>
<P>
Before the insolvency of Halla, the year 1997 had seen
liquidations of five other conglomerates which were among the
country's top 30. But it was the first bankruptcy since the
October financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
A top corporate official said the mounting deficits and debts
of Halla Heavy Industries dealt a heavy blow to the group. He
complained that after the October crisis, financial firms withdrew
their loans and suspended new loans.
</P>
<P>
The group narrowly escaped bankruptcy last Thursday after its
creditor banks provided an emergency loan to help it pay back
defaulted debts worthy of 241.2 billion won(about 209 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The group announced it will apply for court protection for
debt-rescheduling of two subsidiaries, Mando Machinery and Halla
Cement, Halla Construction while seeking court receiveship for
Halla's chief units Halla Heavy Industries and Halla Marine.
</P>
<P>
If creditors accept the group's debt rescheduling conditions,
Halla can be reshaped into a sound company through a tough
reshuffling program in three or four years, the group said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, South Korea's largest conglomerate, Hyundai Group
ruled out the possibility of taking over the affiliates of Halla
Group despite the fact that owners of the two groups are brothers.
</P>
<P>
Hyundai had already done everything it could for Halla,
including the discounting of the group's bills and the purchasing
of commercial papers of its affiliates, an executive official in
Hyundai Group said.
</P>
<P>
Hyundai's financial units, Hyundai Merchant Banking and Hyundai
Securities which have lent Halla up to 800 billion won (about 692
million U.S. dollars), are considering of taking legal steps
toward the ill-fated group, he said.
</P>
<P>
Most of South Korean large conglomerates said that the business
environment is rapidly worsening because it is obvious that
businesses in financial dilemma can no longer expect assistance
from the government or banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971206.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Poverty Alleviation, Hard Task for Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan, a South Asian
nation with a population of approximately 140 million, has made
great endeavors in recent years to reduce the proportion of its
poor people.
</P>
<P>
The government of Pakistan has taken the issue of poverty
alleviation as one of its top priorities.
</P>
<P>
The government initiated the Social Action Program (SAP) in
1992 to attend to the long-existing structural imbalance in
development.
</P>
<P>
The SAP, which included two phases, involves primary education,
basic health, population welfare and rural water supply and
sanitation.
</P>
<P>
The strategy of the program focused on enhancing its coverage
level and on improving the quality of services through sustained
increase in expenditures and specific policy measures in each area
the program covers.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the SAP between 1992 and 1996 produced
satisfactory results. Primary school attending rate rose from 84.8
percent to 89 percent for boys and from 53.7 percent to 57 percent
for girls, while life expectancy of women was improved from 61.2
to 62.9 years.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, contraceptive prevalence rate rose from 14 percent
to 22 percent in the first phase; infant mortality rate decreased
from 101 to 86 per thousand live births; rural water supply
coverage increased from 27 percent to 55 percent and that of rural
sanitation from 13 percent to 23 percent.
</P>
<P>
The government has initiated the second phase of the SAP
(1996-2000) with an expected investment of 270 billion rupees (6.7
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
During the second phase, all indicators of primary school
attending rate, life expectancy for women, contraceptive
prevalence rate and rural water supply coverage are expected to be
improved further.
</P>
<P>
It is encouraging that the government of Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif has set up a Federal Task Force on Poverty Eradication to
help improve its policy framework.
</P>
<P>
The task force has been entrusted to prepare a report on the
trends and magnitude of poverty, dimensions of a macroeconomic
policy and structural changes warranted for reducing poverty.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government has time and again highlighted the
urgency to address policy issues such as investment in human
resources, institutional support packages for services, and
comprehensive training activities for both personnel and community
organizers engaged in poverty alleviation programs.
</P>
<P>
However, it is believed that to make the poverty alleviation
work more effective and fruitful, the government has to balance
the role of the public sector, non-governmental organizations and
donors from all sectors and the approved policy framework.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan now is the eighth most populous nation in the world.
Yet in terms of human development indicators, it ranks 134th among
174 developing countries, a fact which could hardly be ignored.
</P>
<P>
Despite the achievements made in the past few years in
alleviating poverty, the Pakistani government still faces a tough
challenge as about 28 percent of its population are still living
below the poverty line.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971206.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-06 </DATE_TIME>
