<HEADLINE> More Suspected H5N1 Cases Discovered in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Department of
Health today announced the discovery of two more suspected cases
of H5N1 influenza A.
</P>
<P>
The two suspected cases involved a 54-year-old man, who has
died and a 13-year-old girl, who is still in hospital.
</P>
<P>
The laboratory results were available Saturday morning, a
Department spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"The laboratory specimens of the two suspected cases had been
sent urgently to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in
Atlanta, United States for confirmation.
</P>
<P>
"The Hospital Authority has been informed of the initial
findings and has been advised to take appropriate surveillance and
prophylactic measures.
</P>
<P>
Investigation into the two suspected cases is being conducted,
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The Special Working Group on H5N1 set up by the Director of
Health has called an urgent meeting on Sunday and an announcement
will be made after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in
Atlanta will be arriving tonight to participate in the
investigation of the recent H5N1 cases.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman advised that the best way to combat influenza
infection was to build up body resistance by having a proper diet
with adequate exercise and rest.
</P>
<P>
"Good ventilation should be maintained to avoid the spread of
respiratory tract infection," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
