<HEADLINE> Official Candidates for HKSAR Deputies to 9th NPC Determined </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The 54 official candidates
for the 36 deputies of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR) to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) of
China were determined here today.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by the Presidium of the Conference for
Electing the HKSAR Deputies of the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
The 54 candidates were selected from 72 nominees by members of
the 424-strong Election Conference through secret balloting this
morning at the 4th plenary session of the Election Conference held
at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
The 72 were nominated by members of the Election Conference
between November 13 and 28. Each of them had obtained nominations
of at least 10 members of the Election Conference.
</P>
<P>
Today's preliminary election was supervised by Chief Scrutineer
Leung Chun-ying, and eight scrutineers, who are members of the
Election Conference but do not run for the NPC deputies.
</P>
<P>
Before the election began at 9:15 a.m., nominees who are not
members of the Election Conference were allowed to introduce
themselves to members of the Election Conference.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary election was prolonged by a run-off to
determine the last official candidate out of two nominees who got
the same ballots at the first round of vote.
</P>
<P>
The final election of the 36 NPC deputies is scheduled for
December 8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
