<HEADLINE> Manila Extends Emergency Aid to Papua New Guinea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
announced today that his country will extend emergency assistance
to drought-hit Papua New Guinea.
</P>
<P>
According to a press statement issued here, Ramos directed the
Department of Health and the Department of Social Welfare and
Development to extend immediate medical and food assistance to
Papua New Guinea, which is now in the throes of an acute food
shortage as a result of a long dry spell induced by the El Nino
phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said that the Philippine assistance to Papua New Guinea
should not be less than 10,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In a report to Ramos, the Philippine Embassy in Port Moresby
said that at least 100 people have died from starvation and up to
250,000 people are without food right now in Papua New guinea,
where thousands of Filipinos have been working for many years.
