<HEADLINE> S. African Lorry Detained in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican police has detained
in Machaze, south of Manica province, a lorry with South African
license plate which was loaded with 15 engines for military
planes including MIG bomber and helicopters.
</P>
<P>
The Noticias newspaper reported today that the lorry which
belongs to South Africa's Gauteng province was detained on
Thursday when it was trying to cross the border from Machaze to
South Africa, about 400 km from the provincial capital Chimoio.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, the engines on the lorry are not
new, and they are estimated to have been dismantled and stolen
from Beira Air Base, the biggest military airport in central
Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
A white South African was detained for this but his name was
not revealed by the police.
</P>
<P>
During the 16-year-long civil war in Mozambique, the former
Soviet Union had provided Mozambican government army with many
military planes including MIG planes.
</P>
<P>
These planes had long been out of use due to lack of
maintenance as a result of money shortage. 
