<HEADLINE> Cholera Claims 156 in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Some 156 people in
Dodoma Region in central Tanzania had died of cholera between May
and November 30 this year, Daily News reported today.
</P>
<P>
During the period, a total of 2,271 people contracted the
communicable disease, said Dr Meshack Massi, Dodoma Regional
Medical Officer.
</P>
<P>
"The situation may become worse after the onset of the ongoing
long rains," the paper quoted Massi as saying.
</P>
<P>
Dr Massi said until Friday, the region had 11 cholera victims
who were still receiving medical treatment at special centers in
the region.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to local residents to take the killer disease
seriously and urged them to observe basic hygienic regulations,
such as boiling drinking water and keeping the environment clean.
