<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Adopts Resolution on Combating Crime, Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian National Assembly
today passed a resolution containing eight measures to combat
crime and corruption.
</P>
<P>
Under the resolution, a standing committee and an integrated
information system, both in charge of issues concerning crime and
corruption, will be established.
</P>
<P>
The incomes and properties of assembly members, ministers,
municipal leaders, judges and other government staff will also be
made public under the resolution.
</P>
<P>
The resolution instructs the Council of Ministers to work out a
nation-wide strategy to fight crimes and requires the minister of
interior to take institutional and official procedures to improve
efficiency in crime cracking down.
</P>
<P>
The National Assembly would give priority to legislative
procedures in the campaign against crime and corruption, it
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
