<HEADLINE> 79th SFOR Person Killed in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Tom Jennings, a U.S. official
working in the Multinational Stabilization Force (SFOR), was
killed Thursday in a traffic accident, becoming the 79th SFOR
fatality in the Bosnian area.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia's news agency Tanjug quoted the communique released
by the U.S. Embassy in Sarajevo as saying four SFOR vehicles were
involved in the accident when they entered the Bosnian southern
area.
</P>
<P>
Jennings, 49, was the 11th American victim in SFOR in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 79 victims died in traffic accidents or were killed
by mines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
