<HEADLINE> Kazakh Civil Aviation Industry in Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Kazakh government today
urged the transportation and communication departments to work out
plans for developing the Kazakh civil aviation industry, which is
in crisis.
</P>
<P>
At a government meeting chaired by Prime Minister Nurlan
Balgimbaev, leaders of the civil aviation sector said the
country's civil aviation is experiencing its most difficult period
and it was due to lack of proper management.
</P>
<P>
Balgimbaev said the government would make efforts to get the
civil aviation industry out of crisis. He criticized the
transportation and communication departments because of their
plans to develop privatized airline companies.
</P>
<P>
The meeting decided to set up supervisory and registration
organs for the state civil aviation. 
</P>
