<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Exports Rise In First 9 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's exports in the
first three quarters of this year rose by 9.09 percent to 39.49
billion U.S. dollars compared with the same period of last year,
according to the latest official figures.
</P>
<P>
Non-oil and gas exports in the first nine months of the year
rose by 10.27 percent to 30.78 billion dollars, while oil and gas
exports grew by 5.1 percent to 8.67 billion dollars, the Ministry
of Industry and Trade said in a report issued on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Imports in the January-September period this year declined by
0.45 percent to 31.78 billion dollars, of which 2.95 billion
dollars was from oil and gas imports and 28.38 billion dollars
from non-oil and gas imports.
</P>
<P>
The balance of payments also registered a 7.7 billion-dollar
trade surplus in January-September, compared with 4.27 billion
dollars in the same period of last year, said the report.
</P>
</TEXT>
