<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Krajisnik: The Bonn Meeting Must Be Fair to All Parties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The coming meeting in Bonn
over the Bosnian situation must treat equally the two political
entities and three nationalities in Bosnia, the Serbian member of
the Bosnian Presidency said this evening.
</P>
<P>
Momcilo Krajisnik made the remarks in Pale after talks with
United States ambassador in Sarajevo, Ricard Kauzlaric, and Jakov
Gerasimov, Russian charge d'affaires. They discussed the Bonn
meeting of December 9 to 10 of the committee that oversees
implementation of the Dayton peace accords in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Krajisnik said the Bonn meeting should not change the Dayton
Accord.
</P>
<P>
The suggestion of giving more power to the NATO-led
multinational Stabilization Force (SFOR) was unacceptable for
Serbians, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Serbia Republic would fulfill its obligations under the
accord, he stated.
</P>
<P>
But it would harm the peace and stability in Bosnia if somebody
tended to force anything not mentioned in the Dayton accord on
others, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
