<HEADLINE> Marintec China '97 Concluded in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 6 (Xinhua) -- A four-day maritime
conference, Marintec China '97, concluded in Shanghai Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese and overseas participants said that the event which
included seminars, exhibitions and trade talks successfully served
as a chance for the world's shipping circles to exchange views.
</P>
<P>
A business executive from Germany said that the reports
delivered by officials of relevant Chinese government departments
and the mayor of Shanghai have helped overseas participants learn
more about China's shipping industry and the development of
Shanghai Port, which is the country's largest port.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 people from 25 countries and regions attended the
conference which is held every other year in the first week of
December in Shanghai. 
