<HEADLINE> Commercial Billboard to Be Auctioned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 6 (Xinhua) -- An auction is scheduled to be
held on December 18 for a neon-light billboard in a busy street in
the center of Nanjing, capital of Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Both Chinese and overseas enterprises are entitled to vie for
the billboard erected on a building at Nanjing's Drum Tower
Square, which draws thousands of visitors a day.
</P>
<P>
The billboard will be divided into three parts. The main
section is 31.5-meter-long and 7.5-meter-wide and is the largest
neon-light billboard of Jiangsu Province. The offer price is
estimated at 900,000 yuan (108,430 US dollars) a year.
</P>
<P>
The other two parts each measure 25 meters in length and five
meter in width and the offer price is estimated at 800,000
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
