<HEADLINE> Holmes Retains WBC Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Keith Holmes successfully
defended his World Boxing Council (WBC) middleweight title at
Florida on Friday by stopping fellow American Paul Vaden in the
11th round.
</P>
<P>
The victory, also his first fight in 13 months, improved
Holmes's record to 30-1 with 20 knockouts.
</P>
<P>
This was his first defense since Holmes claimed the crown in
March of 1996 by stopping Quincy Taylor in the ninth round.
</P>
<P>
Vaden, whose fight with Holmes was twice postponed, fell to
27-2. His only previous loss came in December of 1995 at the
hands of Terry Norris. 
