<HEADLINE> Mexico City Mayor Promises Improvements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Cuauhtemoc Cardenas,
leader of the Party of Democratic Revolution (PRD) of Mexico,
today assumed the office of mayor of Mexico City.
</P>
<P>
In his inaugural speech read in the presence of President
Ernesto Zedillo, Cardenas said his new government will work to
improve the living standards of more than half-a-million people
who are in a precarious situation in the capital of the country.
</P>
<P>
He also pledged to improve the relationship between the
citizens and the government, set solid bases for short and long
term projects, eliminate corruption and combat crime.
</P>
<P>
Cuauhtemoc Cardenas is the first elected chief of the
government of Mexico City. The post was previously occupied by
people designated by the president of the Republic. 
</P>
