<HEADLINE> Chile, China Promote Mining Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Chile and China today signed
an accord to intensify mining cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two countries will cooperate on
industrial mining policies, analysis of investment conditions and
the exchange of information on mineral resources.
</P>
<P>
They will study the possibility of cooperating in mining
investment projects, feasibility and risk studies and training and
academic exchange.
</P>
<P>
Chile expressed support for China over the establishment of a
group of experts in mining, exploration and energy development, at
the Asian-Pacific Economic Cooperation Forum.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation involved in geology and mineral
resources arrived here on November 30 for a one-week stay. It has
visited the Chuquicamata and La Escondida copper mines. 
</P>
