<HEADLINE> Volcano Erupts in Russian Far East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A volcano situated on the
Kamchatka Peninsula in Russia's Far East erupted today spewing
ashes eight to nine kilometers into the sky, and likely to affect
the flights of the international airlines.
</P>
<P>
The eruption of the Bezymyany volcano would pose no immediate
threat to the settlers nearby, who are located about 30 kilometers
away, local reports said.
</P>
<P>
At 1:41 Moscow time today, an earthquake measuring 5-5.5 on the
Richter scale hit the sea area along the east coast of the
Kamchastka Peninsula. No casualties were reported. 
</P>
