<HEADLINE> Cardoso, Menem To Inaugurate Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Henrique Cardoso and Argentine President Carlos Menem Tuesday will
inaugurate a bridge that links the two countries' two border
cities separated by the Uruguay River.
</P>
<P>
The Bridge of Integration is 1,400 meters long and is built to
link Sao Borja in the Brazilian state of Rio Grande DO Sul and Sao
Tome in the province of Misiones of Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The project costs 31 million U.S. dollars and is being
constructed by a consortium of three Argentine and two Brazilian
companies.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian technicians say the structure will have, as a new
Southern Common Market (Mercosur) route, a monthly flow of some
6,000 trucks.
</P>
<P>
Customs post and police stations of the two countries will be
installed at each end of the bridge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
