<HEADLINE> Two Swedes To Stand Trial on Stadiums Bombings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Two suspects involved in the
bombings of the stadiums in Stockholm and Gothenburg were formally
charged on Friday and will stand trial next week.
</P>
<P>
The bombing happened in August this year when the city was
launching a bid for the 2004 Summer Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Chief prosecutor Eva Regner said that the men, both Swedes,
were on charge of "preparing to devastate public property".
</P>
<P>
The men were likely to be sentenced to two to eight years, but
on this lesser charge the court is at liberty to impose a lower
penalty.
</P>
<P>
A little-known group called "We Who Built Sweden" claimed
responsibility for the bombings, insisting that money should be
spent on social programmes rather than hosting sports events.
</P>
<P>
The 2004 Games were awarded to Athens of Greece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
