<HEADLINE> HK Election Conference Chooses Official Candidates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The Conference for Electing
Deputies of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) to
the 9th National People's Congress (NPC) of China is meeting at
the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center this morning.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting chaired by Tung Chee Hwa, executive chairman
of the Presidium, the 424-strong Election Conference will choose
54 official candidates out of 72 to run for the 36 HKSAR deputies
to the 9th NPC through secret balloting.
</P>
<P>
The 72 were nominated by members of the Election Conference
from November 13 to 28. Each of them had obtained nomination by at
least 10 members of the Election Conference.
</P>
<P>
Today's preliminary election is held because the number of
nominees exceeds the maximum number of candidates of 54, a figure
stipulated by the Election Method.
</P>
<P>
The results of the preliminary election will be announced later
together with the list of 54 official candidates.
</P>
<P>
The final election to choose the 36 NPC deputies is scheduled
for December 8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
