<HEADLINE> Latin American Cultural News Items </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The following are news
items about culture, arts and entertainments in Latin American
countries in the past few days:
</P>
<P>
MANAGUA -- The Nicaraguan Academy of Language, founded in 1928,
accepted poet Mariana Sanson Arguello as its member, the first
time in its history that a woman has become a member.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The sale of the manuscript of the most valued
Argentine literary work, "Martin Fierro", has started a big
controversy in the country over its price and authenticity.
</P>
<P>
It is the first part of author Jose Hernandez's work "Martin
Fierro."
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- The 17th Santiago International Book Fair is being
held from November 21 to December 8.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen foreign countries attended the display.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- The United Nations Education, Science and Culture
Organization (UNESCO) declared 46 sites in the world as cultural
heritages of humanity, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
One of those sites is Sao Luis in the state of Maranhao of
Brazil.
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- The Canadian government has returned 124
archeological pieces to Mexico, Colombia and Peru. They were
illegally exported to Canada at the end of the 1980s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
