<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Manila Times
</P>
<P>
-- Amid widespread public criticism of the failure of the
police to stop and solve kidnappings in the Philippines, President
Fidel Ramos Friday accepted the resignation of National Police
Director General Recaredo Sarmiento.
</P>
<P>
Manila Standard
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippine National Democratic Front, in a move seen by
many as an indication of their willingness to have the stalled
peace talks with the government resumed, freed a police chief and
an army sergeant Friday.
</P>
<P>
Today
</P>
<P>
-- The recent increase in oil prices, the currency crisis and
the slower growth of the economy have finally taken their toll on
consumer prices, resulting in a 6.5 percent inflation rate in
November, 0.8 percent higher than the previous month.  
