<HEADLINE> Hingis, Majoli Remain Unbeaten </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 5 (Xinhua) -- World number one Martina Hingis
and Iva Majoli remained unbeaten at the Masters of Champions
tennis tournament and advanced into the semi-finals at Frankfurt
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hingis beat Anke Huber of Germany 6-4, 7-6 (7-3). Earlier in
the tournament, Hingis beat Mary Pierce of France and Amanda
Coetzer of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Majoli needed three sets to beat Lindsay Davenport of the
United States 2-6, 6-2, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Majoli, the French Open titlist, previously beat Irina Spirlea
of Romania and Mary Joe Fernandez of the United States.
</P>
<P>
In other actions on Friday, Spirlea defeated Fernandez 6-3, 6-3
and Pierce beat Coetzer 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
