<HEADLINE> Egypt's Zamalek Wins Afro-Asian Football Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Egypt's Zamalek claimed the title
of the Afro-Asian Football Tournament as the club's golden boy
Mohammed Sabri scored the winner in a nail-biting match on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Zamalek beat Yohang 1-0, avenging its 1-2 loss to the best
South Korean club team during their previous encounter in Seoul,
the capital of South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the kickoff, the young Pharaohs dominated the
pitch and their relentless offensive turned out several
near-goals, leaving the Korean guards scrambling to keep the gate
clean.
</P>
<P>
In the 12th minute, Sabri turned a long pass into a strong
right kick outside the penalty area. The ball flew to the left of
the net and Korean goalie failed to pluck it out.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the South Korean team turned up the heat
and organized a string of fast offensives in front of the gate,
but failed to get an equalizer.
</P>
<P>
Zamalek, the African football club championship title-holder,
is Egypt's best football club after Ahli. 
</P>
</TEXT>
