<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Rise Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Stocks rallied on Wall Street
Friday, setting new highs for the first time in nearly two months,
as a surprisingly strong economic report eased worries about weak
profits.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 98.97 points to 8,149.13,
just 110 points shy of its all-time best close at 8,159.31 on
August 6.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 stock index and the New York Stock
Exchange composite index set new highs. The two broad-market
measures closed at record highs for the first time since October 7.
</P>
<P>
For the week, the Dow gained 326 points, or more than 4 percent,
giving it a 26 percent gain for 1997 with less than a month to go.
The S&AMP;P 500 and the NYSE composite are both up more than 30 percent
this year.
</P>
<P>
In a report that normally would have pulled down the market, the
Labor Department said the nation's unemployment rate sank to a
24-year low of 4.6 percent in November.
</P>
<P>
The report did, in fact, affect the inflation-sensitive bond
market. As bond prices fell, the yield on the 30-year Treasury
rose as high as 6.16 percent before settling at 6.09 percent. That
compares with late Thursday's 6.04 percent and late Wednesday's
6.01 percent, which was the lowest finish since January 1996,
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a 3-to-2 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume slowed from the hectic
pace seen Wednesday and Thursday, but still totaled a brisk 556.93
million shares.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 rose 10.69 to 983.79, beating its
previous best finish of 983.12. The NYSE composite rose 4.87 to
514.31, moving past the prior record of 514.21.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index, laden with technology issues
believed most vulnerable to the turmoil in Asia, rose 20.48 to
1,633.90, but still sits more than 100 points from record
territory.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 3.15 to 438.06,
and the small-company dominated American Stock Exchange composite
index rose 4.47 to 670.27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
