<HEADLINE> Goodwill Games to Award Prize Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Goodwill Games will
award prize money for the first time to track and field athletes
and bonus money for world records.
</P>
<P>
The largest bonus for the 1998 Goodwill Games will be 100,000
U.S. dollars. The prize will be awarded to an athlete setting a
world record in some of the men's or women's track and field
events.
</P>
<P>
The 50,000 U.S. dollars bonus money will be awarded to an
athlete who sets world record in the men's or women's triple jump,
discus, shot put, hammer throw and javelin, along with the men's
20 kilometers walk and the women's 10 kilometers walk and pole
vault.
</P>
<P>
Event winners will also receive prize money ranging from 6,000
to 40,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 Goodwill Games will be held from July 19 to August 2
in New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
