<HEADLINE> Conference on European Expansion Opens in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The two-day conference of
"European enlargement and southeastern Europe" opened here today
to discuss the expansion of the European Union (EU) and its
affects on southeastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
The conference, with the participation of 34 representatives of
political parties, institutes from Balkan and European countries
is being organized by the Institute for Strategic and Development
Studies. It also focuses on the political and economic situation
in southeastern Europe, the institutional reconstruction of Balkan
states, minorities and a civil society, as well as multicultural
Balkan societies within national boundaries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the conference, European Parliament Vice President
Paraskevas Avgerinos said today that he was sceptical about
whether the EU budget would be able to meet the requirements of
expansion. He also expressed fears as to the cost to southern
states.
</P>
<P>
As for the proposed European conference for states wishing to
join the EU, Avgerinos insisted that the majority of members of
the European Parliament were against holding such a conference,
preferring that only "democratic states" be invited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
