<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief to Visit Iran, Kuwait, Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General of the
United Nations Kofi Annan is scheduled to visit Iran, Kuwait and
Malaysia from December 6-17, Annan's spokesman announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Traveling vie London, Annan will be in Tehran on December 8 for
an official visit to Iran, spokesman Fred Eckhard said.
</P>
<P>
Annan is to address a summit of the Organization of Islamic
Conference to be held in Tehran from December 9 to 11.
</P>
<P>
From Tehran, Annan will go to Kuwait to pay an official visit
to the country while making a side trip to the U.N. Iraq-Kuwait
Observation Mission (UNIKOM) from December 12-14.
</P>
<P>
The Secretary-General's official visit to Malaysia is set for
December 14-17.  
</P>
</TEXT>
